import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='people', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population growth over time?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    age_dist = data.groupby('age')['people'].sum().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='age', y='people', data=age_dist)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age groups in the population?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    
    gender_counts = data['sex'].value_counts()
    gender_counts.index = ['Male', 'Female']
    
    plt.pie(gender_counts, labels=gender_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the population?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
